body_content.explanation: a group of vitamins (= natural substances that are necessary in small amounts for the growth and good health of the body) that dissolve in water and are found in food:
examples: Found in foods such as brewer's yeast, wheat germ and liver, vitamin B complex is vital for processing the energy transfer from food to fuel.
What was formerly thought to be a single vitamin and called Water Soluble B is now called the vitamin B complex. It is not one vitamin but many that occur together.
These symptoms may also be linked to a vitamin B complex deficiency.
